{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603597","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603597"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:40:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:40:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15768"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15768","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15768"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.24,0.08,0.56,0.04,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8459"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67684"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8459","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8459"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15768"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53144"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7053"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20344"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20347"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22676"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67684","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67684"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe penis receives its blood supply from a single main artery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following arteries provides the main blood supply to this organ?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["External pudendal artery","Inferior vesical artery","Internal pudendal artery","Obturator artery","Superior vesical artery"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal pudendal artery\u003C/strong\u003E is the main arterial supply to the penis. It branches from the anterior division of the internal iliac artery and continues through Alcock\u0027s canal before giving rise to the dorsal and deep arteries of the penis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior vesical artery\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior vesical artery\u003C/strong\u003E supply the urinary bladder and do not contribute significantly to penile blood supply. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eobturator artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the adductor compartment of the thigh. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal pudendal artery\u003C/strong\u003E, a branch of the femoral artery, only supplies the skin of the external genitalia.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The penis receives its arterial supply primarily from the internal pudendal artery, which gives rise to the dorsal and deep arteries of the penis","The internal pudendal artery is a branch of the anterior division of the internal iliac artery"],"references":["Dean RC, Lue TF. Physiology of penile erection and pathophysiology of erectile dysfunction. Urol Clin North Am. 2005 Nov;32(4):379-95, v. doi: 10.1016/j.ucl.2005.08.007. PMID: 16291031; PMCID: PMC1351051.","Foster RA. Male Genital System. Jubb, Kennedy \u0026 Palmer\u0027s Pathology of Domestic Animals: Volume 3. 2016:465\u2013510.e1. doi: 10.1016/B978-0-7020-5319-1.00016-5. Epub 2016 Mar 18. PMCID: PMC7271154.","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media.","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53144"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15768"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"ite